    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Archaeological term for the secondary shaping of a stone core or implement after initial manufacture. Small fragments are removed to sharpen, straighten, or thin the core.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
